[SN]TITLE[SN]
Charlton Athletic P-P Scunthorpe United

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Charlton Athletic's League One match against Scunthorpe United has been postponed because of a frozen pitch.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Referee Dean Whitestone inspected the playing surface at The Valley at 10:00 GMT before calling the game off shortly after.
Temperatures had dropped to below freezing in the capital overnight.
Charlton are 11th in the third tier, while Scunthorpe are second having only lost four of their 27 matches so far this campaign.
